Only one article mentions freedom of speech:

1. [constitution_india.pdf, Article 19(1)_p1]
19. Protection of certain rights regarding freedom of speech, etc.—
(1) All citizens shall have the right— 
(a) to freedom of speech and expression; 
(b) to assemble peaceably and without arms; 
(c) to form associations or unions 2[or co-operative societies]; 
(d) to move freely throughout the territory of India; 

(w.e.f. 14-1-2019).

There are no articles in [constitution_pak.pdf] that specifically mention freedom of speech.
